                  </persName>
             FONTAINE. I paid the prisoner in a check for ten pounds ten shillings, for which he gave me that receipt.</p>
               <p>JOSEPH METCALF. I am clerk to Messrs. Smith, Payne, and Smith, who are Mr. De Fontaine's bankers. I paid that check, but I don't know to whom. (check read.) Receipt read appearing to be a receipt for the sum of ten pounds ten shillings, given by the prisoner on the account of his employers, to Mr. De Fontaine, and signed by the prisoner for and on such account.</p>
